  "prompt": "What is demand?",
  "response": "Demand refers to the quantity of a good or service that consumers are willing and able to purchase at various prices during a given period of time. It is a fundamental concept in economics that reflects the desire and ability of consumers to buy products. Demand can be influenced by several factors, including price, income levels, consumer preferences, the prices of related goods, expectations about future prices, and demographic trends.\n\nThe relationship between the price of a good and the quantity demanded is typically represented by the demand curve, which is usually downward sloping. This indicates that as the price of a good decreases, the quantity demanded generally increases, and vice versa. This inverse relationship is known as the law of demand.",
